properties.subject: Mount Fitz Roy
properties.description: Mount Fitz Roy is a mountain in Patagonia, on the border between Argentina and Chile. It is located in the Southern Patagonian Ice Field, near El Chalt√©n village and Viedma Lake. The mountain is the symbol of the Argentine Santa Cruz Province, which includes its representation on its coat of arms.

properties.subject: Rocky Mountain Elk
properties.description: The Rocky Mountain elk is a subspecies of elk found in the Rocky Mountains and adjacent ranges of Western North America. The winter ranges are most common in open forests and floodplain marshes in the lower elevations. In the summer it migrates to the subalpine forests and alpine basins. The total wild population is about one million individuals.

properties.subject: Tukad Cepung Waterfall
properties.description: Tukad Cepung Waterfall is a beautiful hidden waterfall in Bali, Indonesia. It is a unique waterfall because it is located in a cave. To get to the waterfall, visitors need to walk through the jungle and wade through a knee-deep river. The sunlight falls on the glistening waterfall creating a rainbow, which feels as though it is projected right up to you.

properties.subject: Silfra Rift
properties.description: Silfra is a rift that is part of the divergent tectonic boundary between the North American and Eurasian plates. It is located in Thingvellir National Park in Iceland. The rift was formed in 1789 by the earthquakes accompanying the divergent movement of the two tectonic plates. The Silfra fissure is one of the most popular diving and snorkeling spots in Iceland.

properties.subject: Dan Hotel, Tel Aviv
properties.description: The Dan Tel Aviv Hotel is a hotel in Tel Aviv

properties.subject: Embarcadero Center
properties.description: The Embarcadero Center is a commercial complex of five office towers and two hotels on a 9.8-acre (4.0 ha) site located off the Embarcadero in the financial district of San Francisco, California. Developed by Trammell Crow, David Rockefeller, and John Portman, construction began with Tower One in 1971, with the last off-complex extension, Embarcadero West, completed in 1989.

properties.subject: Lake Kawaguchi
properties.description: Lake Kawaguchi is a very popular tourist destination near Mount Fuji. The lake is located in Fujikawaguchiko, Yamanashi Prefecture, Japan. It is the second largest of the Fuji Five Lakes in terms of surface area, and is located at the lowest elevation. It is situated at an altitude of approximately 800 metres, which accounts for its relatively cool summers and frequently icy winters.

properties.subject: Baker Beach
properties.description: Baker Beach is a public beach on the peninsula of San Francisco, California, U.S.. The beach lies on the shore of the Pacific Ocean to the northwest of the city. It is roughly a half mile long, beginning just south of Golden Gate Point, extending southward toward the Seacliff peninsula, the Palace of the Legion of Honor and the Sutro Baths.

properties.subject: Vaidyeshvara temple
properties.description: The Vaidyeshvara temple is a Hindu temple located in Talakad, a town on the left bank of the Kaveri river in the Indian state of Karnataka. It is one of the Panchalinga temples dedicated to the Hindu god Shiva. The temple is located in the Chola region of South India. The temple is protected as a monument of national importance by the Archaeological Survey of India.

properties.subject: Times Square
properties.description: Times Square is a major commercial and entertainment hub in the heart of New York City. It is located at the junction of Broadway and Seventh Avenue and stretches from West 42nd to West 47th Streets. Brightly adorned with billboards and advertisements, Times Square is sometimes referred to as The Crossroads of the World, The Center of the Universe, and the heart of The Great White Way.

properties.subject: Long-tailed tit
properties.description: The long-tailed tit is a common bird found throughout Europe and the Palearctic.

properties.subject: Starfish
properties.description: The Costa de la Luz is a section of the Andalusian coast in Spain facing the Atlantic. It extends from Tarifa in the south, along the coasts of the Province of C√°diz and the Province of Huelva, to the mouth of the Guadiana River.

properties.subject: Eurasian bullfinch
properties.description: Bia≈Çowie≈ºa National Park is a national park in Podlaskie Voivodeship, in Eastern Poland adjacent with the border with Belarus. The park is known for its unique blend of temperate and boreal flora and fauna, including the European bison, the continent's heaviest land animals.

properties.subject: Bamboo Grove
properties.description: The Bamboo Forest is a natural forest of bamboo in Arashiyama, Kyoto, Japan. The forest consists of several pathways for tourists and visitors. The Ministry of the Environment considers it a part of the soundscape of Japan.

properties.subject: Aspen Trees
properties.description: The Uncompahgre National Forest is a U.S. National Forest covering 955,229 acres in (1,492.55 sq mi, or 3,865.68 km¬≤) in parts of Montrose, Mesa, San Miguel, Ouray, Gunnison, Hinsdale, San Juan, and Delta Counties in western Colorado. Only its headquarters is in Delta County, in the city of Delta. It borders the San Juan National Forest to the south.

properties.subject: The Narrows
properties.description: The Narrows is the narrowest section of Zion Canyon in Zion National Park, Utah, United States. Situated on the North Fork of the Virgin River and upstream of the main canyon, The Narrows is one of the premier hikes in the park and on the Colorado Plateau.

properties.subject: Abraham Lake
properties.description: Abraham Lake is an artificial lake on North Saskatchewan River in western Alberta, Canada. Abraham Lake has a surface area of 53.7 km2 (20.7 sq mi) and a length of 32 km (20 mi). It was built on the upper course of the North Saskatchewan River, in the foothills of the Canadian Rockies. It lines David Thompson Highway between Saskatchewan River Crossing and Nordegg.

properties.subject: Hot Air Balloons over Goreme
properties.description: G√∂reme, located among the 'fairy chimney' rock formations, is a town in Cappadocia, a historical region of Turkey. It is in the Nev≈üehir Province in Central Anatolia and has a population of around 2,000 people. The G√∂reme National Park was added to the UNESCO World Heritage List in 1985.

properties.subject: Tre Cime di Lavaredo
properties.description: The Tre Cime di Lavaredo, also called the Drei Zinnen, are three distinctive battlement-like peaks, in the Sexten Dolomites of northeastern Italy. They are probably one of the best-known mountain groups in the Alps. The three peaks, from east to west, are: Cima Piccola ('little peak'), Cima Grande ('big peak'), and Cima Ovest ('western peak').

properties.subject: Oakland Bay Bridge
properties.description: The San Francisco‚ÄìOakland Bay Bridge, known locally as the Bay Bridge, is a complex of bridges spanning San Francisco Bay in California. As part of Interstate 80 and the direct road between San Francisco and Oakland, it carries about 260,000 vehicles a day on its two decks.

properties.subject: Dutch windmill
properties.description: The Netherlands is famous for its windmills. The windmills are a symbol of the Dutch struggle with water. The windmills were used to pump water out of the lowlands and to grind grain. The windmills are a popular tourist attraction in the Netherlands.

properties.subject: Mount Rainier
properties.description: Mount Rainier is the highest mountain in the U.S. state of Washington and a major feature of the Cascade Range. It is the most topographically prominent mountain in the contiguous United States and the Cascade Volcanic Arc, with a summit elevation of 14,411 ft (4,392 m).

properties.subject: Buachaille Etive M√≤r
properties.description: Buachaille Etive M√≤r is a mountain at the head of Glen Etive in the Highlands of Scotland. Its almost perfect pyramidal form, as seen from the A82 road when travelling towards Glen Coe, makes it one of the most recognisable mountains in Scotland, and one of the most depicted on postcards and calendars.

properties.subject: Rotenberg ob der Tauber
properties.description: Rothenburg ob der Tauber is a town in the district of Ansbach of Mittelfranken (Middle Franconia), the Franconia region of Bavaria, Germany. It is well known for its well-preserved medieval old town, a destination for tourists from around the world. It is part of the popular Romantic Road through southern Germany.

properties.subject: Downtown San Francisco
properties.description: Treasure Island is an artificial island in the San Francisco Bay and a neighborhood in the city and county of San Francisco. Built 1936‚Äì37 for the 1939 Golden Gate International Exposition, the island's World's Fair site is a California Historical Landmark. Buildings there have been listed on the National Register of Historic Places, and the historical Naval Station Treasure Island, an auxiliary air facility, are designated in the Geographic Names Information System.

properties.subject: Riomaggiore
properties.description: Riomaggiore is a village and comune in the province of La Spezia, situated in a small valley in the Liguria region of Italy. It is the first of the Cinque Terre one meets when traveling north from La Spezia. The village, dating from the early thirteenth century, is known for its historic character and its wine, produced by the town's vineyards. Riomaggiore is in the Riviera di Levante region and has a shoreline on the Mediterranean's Gulf of Genoa, with a small beach and a wharf framed by tower houses.

properties.subject: King Penguin
properties.description: South Georgia is an island in the southern Atlantic Ocean that is part of the British Overseas Territory of South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands. The island is a haven for wildlife, with colonies of king penguins, albatrosses, and other birds, as well as elephant and fur seals. The island is also home to the South Georgia Museum, which covers the island's history and wildlife.

properties.subject: Rainbow Mountains of the Danxia Landform in Zhangye, China
properties.description: Zhangye National Geopark is located in Sunan and Linze counties within the prefecture-level city of Zhangye, in Gansu, China. It covers an area of 322 square kilometres (124 sq mi). The site became a quasi-national geopark on April 23, 2012. It was formally designated as a national geopark on June 16, 2016. Known for its colorful rock formations, it has been voted by Chinese media outlets as one of the most beautiful landforms in China.

properties.subject: Bella Tola
properties.description: Bella Tola is a mountain of the Swiss Pennine Alps, located west of the Weisshorn. It lies in the Bernese Oberland, on the border between the cantons of Valais and Bern. The mountain is known for its panoramic views of the Bernese Alps and the Rh√¥ne Valley.

properties.subject: Fanad Head Lighthouse
properties.description: Fanad is a peninsula that lies between Lough Swilly and Mulroy Bay on the north coast of County Donegal, Ireland.

properties.subject: Bondi Beach
properties.description: Bondi Beach is a popular beach and the name of the surrounding suburb in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia.

properties.subject: Lake Louise
properties.description: Banff National Park is Canada's oldest national park, established in 1885 as Rocky Mountains Park.

properties.subject: Wat Sirindhorn Wararam Phu Phrao
properties.description: Wat Sirindhorn Wararam is a temple in Ubon Ratchathani, Thailand. It is also known as Wat Phu Prao. The temple is located on a hilltop and offers panoramic views of the surrounding area. The temple is known for its beautiful architecture and serene atmosphere.

properties.subject: Port of Barcelona
properties.description: The Port of Barcelona is a major seaport located in Barcelona, Spain. Along with the Port of Tarragona, it is one of Catalonia's two major seaports and one of the largest ports in the Mediterranean Sea.

properties.subject: Times Square
properties.description: Times Square is a major commercial and entertainment hub in the heart of New York City. It is located at the junction of Broadway and Seventh Avenue and stretches from West 42nd to West 47th Streets. Brightly adorned with billboards and advertisements, Times Square is sometimes referred to as The Crossroads of the World, The Center of the Universe, and the heart of The Great White Way.

properties.subject: Bara Shigri Glacier
properties.description: Bara Shigri Glacier is the largest glacier in Himachal Pradesh, India. It is situated in the Chandra Valley of Lahaul and Spiti district. The glacier is 25 km long and is the second longest glacier in the Indian Himalayas after Gangotri Glacier. The glacier is the source of the Chandra River, which is a major tributary of the Chenab River.

properties.subject: Senteniel Rock
properties.description: Sentinel Rock is a granitic peak in Yosemite National Park, California, United States. It towers over Yosemite Valley, opposite Yosemite Falls. Sentinel Rock lies 0.7 miles (1.1 km) northwest of Sentinel Dome.

properties.subject: Dead Sea
properties.description: The Dead Sea is a landlocked salt lake bordered by Jordan to the east and the Israeli-occupied West Bank and Israel to the west. It lies in the Jordan Rift Valley, and its main tributary is the Jordan River.

properties.subject: Arkadi Monastery
properties.description: The Arkadi Monastery is an Eastern Orthodox monastery, situated on a fertile plateau 23 km (14 mi) to the southeast of Rethymnon on the island of Crete in Greece.

properties.subject: Big Ben
properties.description: Big Ben is the nickname for the Great Bell of the Great Clock of Westminster at the north end of the Palace of Westminster in London, England, and is usually extended to refer to both the clock and the clock tower. The official name of the tower in which Big Ben is located was originally the Clock Tower, but it was renamed Elizabeth Tower in 2012 to mark the Diamond Jubilee of Elizabeth II.
